results.name: Expansion of Product_{k>=1} (1 - q^(10k-5))^2.
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..5000
formula: a(5*n) = A022597(n). a(n) = 0 unless n == 0 (mod 5). - _Michael Somos_, Jun 08 2012
mathematica: A022597[n_] := SeriesCoefficient[ Product[1 + q^k, {k, n}]^-2, {q, 0, n}]; a[n_] := If[Mod[n, 5] != 0, 0, A022597[n/5]]; a[0] = 1; Table[a[n], {n, 0, 96}] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Nov 12 2012, after _Michael Somos_ *)
program: (MAGMA) m:=100; R<x>:=PowerSeriesRing(Integers(), m); Coefficients(R!( (&*[(1-x^(10*k-5))^2: k in [1..20]]))); // _G. C. Greubel_, Oct 20 2018
results.author: _Eric W. Weisstein_, Nov 12 2003
